---
apiVersion: "mcp.ypipe.com/v1"
kind: "McpIntegrationBlueprint"
metadata:
  name: "msoffice"
  namespace: "system"
spec:
  displayName: "Microsoft Office  / Office 365"
  description: "A Model Context Protocol server for Microsoft 365. It enables interaction\
    \ with Outlook, Calendar, Teams, and OneNote through the Microsoft Graph API."
  configurationSchema: {}
  mcpConfig:
    type: "stdio"
    command: "npx"
    args:
    - "-y"
    - "@softeria/ms-365-mcp-server"
    - "--org-mode"
    env: null
    url: null
    headers: null
  disabledTools:
  - "verify-login"
  - "select-account"
  - "list-accounts"
  - "remove-account"
  - "delete-mail-message"
  - "delete-mail-attachment"
  - "list-outlook-contacts"
  - "delete-outlook-contact"
  - "delete-calendar-event"
  - "delete-specific-calendar-event"
  - "list-drives"
  - "list-folder-files"
  - "get-drive-root-item"
  - "download-onedrive-file-content"
  - "upload-file-content"
  - "search-sharepoint-sites"
  - "get-sharepoint-site"
  - "list-sharepoint-site-drives"
  - "get-sharepoint-site-drive-by-id"
  - "get-sharepoint-site-by-path"
  - "list-sharepoint-site-items"
  - "get-sharepoint-site-item"
  - "list-sharepoint-site-lists"
  - "get-sharepoint-site-list"
  - "list-sharepoint-site-list-items"
  - "get-sharepoint-site-list-item"
  - "get-sharepoint-sites-delta"
  - "delete-onedrive-file"
  - "list-excel-worksheets"
  - "get-excel-range"
  - "create-excel-chart"
  - "format-excel-range"
  - "sort-excel-range"
  - "list-todo-task-lists"
  - "list-todo-tasks"
  - "create-todo-task"
  - "get-todo-task"
  - "update-todo-task"
  - "delete-todo-task"
  - "list-planner-tasks"
  - "get-planner-plan"
  - "list-plan-tasks"
  - "create-planner-task"
  - "get-planner-task"
  - "update-planner-task"
  - "update-planner-task-details"
  suggestions: []
  tools:
    get-current-user:
      description: "Retrieve the current user's profile details."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Retrieve the comprehensive profile details and organizational\
        \ identity of the currently authenticated Microsoft 365 user. This tool fetches\
        \ data directly from the Microsoft Graph '/me' endpoint, providing a wealth\
        \ of context about the user's role and presence. The returned information\
        \ includes the user's full display name, primary SMTP email address, job title\
        \ (e.g., 'Senior Software Engineer'), office location, department, and a unique,\
        \ immutable user ID (GUID). Behavioral notes: The availability of specific\
        \ fields depends on the data populated in the organization's Azure Active\
        \ Directory (AAD) and the privacy settings of the user. Use cases: Personalizing\
        \ AI-human interactions ('Hello, Sarah! How can I help with your tasks today?'),\
        \ identifying the user's organizational context to intelligently route emails,\
        \ finding the sender's own email address for adding CC or BCC recipients to\
        \ a message, and verifying that the correct account is being used for a sensitive\
        \ task. Keywords: user profile, identity management, Microsoft account, personal\
        \ info, job title, organizational context, AAD profile, SMTP address, GUID,\
        \ employee information. Caveats: Some fields may be null or empty if the IT\
        \ department has not filled them in. This tool allows the AI to understand\
        \ exactly 'who' it is acting on behalf of, enabling a more personalized, contextually\
        \ aware, and professional assistant experience. It ensures that the AI can\
        \ answer questions about the user's own identity and use that information\
        \ to intelligently interact with colleagues, schedule meetings in the correct\
        \ time zone, and maintain a consistent professional persona across all Microsoft\
        \ 365 services. It is the key to providing a truly integrated 'digital twin'\
        \ experience for the user, ensuring all actions are contextually appropriate\
        \ for the user's specific role."
      properties: null
      required: null
    list-calendars:
      description: "Retrieve a list of user calendars."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Retrieve a comprehensive, detailed list of all calendars associated\
        \ with the user's Microsoft 365 account. This tool provides visibility into\
        \ the user's entire scheduling landscape, including the primary 'Calendar'\
        \ (the default for most appointments), any additional personal calendars created\
        \ for specific purposes (e.g., 'Travel', 'Personal Projects', 'Family'), and\
        \ any shared calendars from colleagues, teams, or external organizations that\
        \ the user has been granted access to. Behavioral notes: The tool returns\
        \ the display name, assigned color, and a unique, immutable ID for each calendar.\
        \ Use cases: Identifying the most appropriate calendar for a new meeting request,\
        \ finding shared team schedules to coordinate a group event, and auditing\
        \ the user's available time sources to ensure no conflicts exist across different\
        \ life/work areas. Keywords: calendar discovery, schedule management, Outlook\
        \ calendars, shared schedules, hierarchy, time management, calendar ID, schedule\
        \ listing, time resource mapping, calendar auditing. Caveats: Access to shared\
        \ or delegated calendars is strictly dependent on the permissions granted\
        \ by the original owners or the organization's IT policy. This tool is the\
        \ critical first step in any scheduling or time-management task, allowing\
        \ the AI to understand the full 'map' of the user's time commitments. By knowing\
        \ exactly what calendars are available and what they represent, the AI can\
        \ intelligently offer suggestions for meeting locations, check for conflicts\
        \ across multiple disparate schedules, and ensure that the user's time is\
        \ managed holistically and with full awareness of their various professional\
        \ and personal obligations. It is the foundation of a proactive and reliable\
        \ digital scheduling assistant, providing the structural context needed for\
        \ any time-based reasoning."
      properties: null
      required: null
    list-mail-folders:
      description: "List all available mail folders."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Retrieve a complete, hierarchical list of all mail folders and\
        \ subfolders within the user's Microsoft 365 account. This includes all the\
        \ system-standard folders such as 'Inbox' (the primary landing zone for incoming\
        \ mail), 'Sent Items' (the record of all outbound communication), 'Drafts'\
        \ (work-in-progress messages), 'Deleted Items' (Trash for temporary storage\
        \ of discarded mail), 'Junk Email' (for filtered spam), and 'Archive' (for\
        \ long-term storage of processed items), as well as every custom folder and\
        \ subfolder the user has created to organize their communications. Behavioral\
        \ notes: The tool returns the unique display name and the immutable folder\
        \ ID for each entry, which is absolutely necessary for moving messages between\
        \ folders or for performing targeted searches within a specific part of the\
        \ mailbox. Use cases: Navigating a complex mailbox structure, identifying\
        \ where specialized project-related emails are being stored, helping the user\
        \ reorganize their communications into a more consistent hierarchy, and verifying\
        \ the existence of a specific folder before attempting a move operation. Keywords:\
        \ mail organization, folder navigation, Outlook structure, mailbox management,\
        \ hierarchy, taxonomy, folder ID, path discovery, subfolder listing, mail\
        \ architecture. Caveats: Deeply nested folder structures may require recursive\
        \ traversal or multiple targeted calls depending on how the Microsoft Graph\
        \ API exposes the hierarchy. This tool allows the AI to understand the 'map'\
        \ of how the user categorizes their communications, enabling it to assist\
        \ with high-level organization and ensuring that no important message is ever\
        \ 'lost' in an obscure subfolder. It provides the essential structural context\
        \ needed to perform complex mail management tasks, such as 'Move all invoices\
        \ received this month to the Finance/Invoices folder', ensuring that the user's\
        \ digital workspace remains tidy, logical, and easily searchable. It is the\
        \ foundational tool for any automated inbox management or organizational strategy."
      properties: null
      required: null
    create-calendar-event:
      description: "Schedule a new meeting or event."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Schedule and book a new meeting, appointment, or reminder directly\
        \ on the user's Microsoft 365 calendar. This tool provides full control over\
        \ the event's properties, allowing the AI to set the subject line, the physical\
        \ or virtual location (e.g., 'Conference Room A' or a Teams link), the exact\
        \ start and end times, a detailed body description or agenda, and a list of\
        \ invited attendees. Behavioral notes: Upon a successful call, the tool can\
        \ automatically send out meeting invitations to all listed attendees, ensuring\
        \ they receive the request in their own inboxes and can respond accordingly.\
        \ Use cases: Booking a discovery call with a new client, setting up an internal\
        \ team brainstorm session, blocking off 'focus time' for deep work, and adding\
        \ a reminder for an important project milestone or deadline. Keywords: meeting\
        \ scheduling, appointment creation, Outlook calendar, event booking, time\
        \ allocation, invitation management, calendar entry, meeting dispatch, schedule\
        \ addition, appointment booking. Caveats: The AI should always perform a check\
        \ for existing conflicts using 'get-calendar-view' or 'find-meeting-times'\
        \ before finalizing a booking to ensure the user's availability. It is also\
        \ critical to ensure that the time zone is correctly specified to avoid confusing\
        \ scheduling errors across different regions. This tool empowers the AI to\
        \ actively manage and protect the user's time, turning plans and intentions\
        \ into concrete, professional commitments. It is a powerful utility for organizational\
        \ coordination, ensuring that everyone is aligned and that the user's schedule\
        \ accurately reflects their current priorities, obligations, and workload,\
        \ thus serving as a truly capable executive assistant. It transforms plans\
        \ into action."
      properties: null
      required: null
    create-draft-email:
      description: "Create and save a new draft email."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Compose and save a new email message as a draft in the user's\
        \ Outlook account without sending it to the recipients. This tool is a key\
        \ enabler of a collaborative 'AI-drafts, user-sends' workflow, where the AI\
        \ performs the heavy lifting of gathering information and drafting a response,\
        \ but the user retains final creative and editorial control. Behavioral notes:\
        \ The draft is saved in the user's 'Drafts' folder and can be further refined,\
        \ edited, or sent through the standard Outlook web/desktop interface or by\
        \ using the 'send-mail' tool at a later time. Use cases: Preparing a highly\
        \ complex response to a client that requires a final 'human' check for nuance,\
        \ staging several related emails for a coordinated project launch, and saving\
        \ a work-in-progress message when the AI needs more information before completion.\
        \ Keywords: draft composition, message staging, Outlook drafts, preparation,\
        \ collaborative writing, email drafting, content staging, work-in-progress.\
        \ Caveats: Drafts are not sent automatically and will sit in the folder indefinitely\
        \ until acted upon by a human or another tool call. The AI must clearly inform\
        \ the user that a draft has been created and where it can be found. This tool\
        \ is an excellent way for the AI to provide significant value while remaining\
        \ safely 'in the loop', allowing the user to maintain ultimate control over\
        \ their outbound communications and organizational voice. It ensures that\
        \ the AI can handle the time-consuming work of content creation while leaving\
        \ the critical decision-making process of when and how to communicate to the\
        \ user, providing a perfect balance between automation efficiency and human\
        \ oversight. It is the ideal tool for high-stakes communication where human\
        \ approval is mandatory."
      properties: null
      required: null
    send-chat-message:
      description: "Post a new message to a Teams chat."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Compose and post a brand new instant message to a specific 1-on-1\
        \ or group chat in Microsoft Teams. This tool allows the AI to participate\
        \ actively in real-time conversations, providing quick status updates, answering\
        \ questions from colleagues, or sharing important links and documents. Behavioral\
        \ notes: The message is delivered instantly to all participants in the chat\
        \ and will trigger a notification on their devices. Use cases: Poking a colleague\
        \ for an urgent update on a task, sharing a concise summary of a completed\
        \ work item in a project chat, and providing an automated but helpful response\
        \ to a common team query. Keywords: Teams messaging, instant response, chat\
        \ participation, real-time update, communication, IM, message dispatch, chat\
        \ post, real-time collaboration, instant notification. Caveats: Just like\
        \ with emails, once a Teams chat message is sent, it is immediately visible\
        \ to all participants. The AI must be extremely careful to ensure that the\
        \ tone is appropriate for the informal but professional context of a chat\
        \ and that no sensitive information is shared inappropriately. This tool gives\
        \ the AI a 'voice' in the user's most immediate and high-frequency communication\
        \ channel, enabling it to act as a proactive, responsive, and truly helpful\
        \ team member. It ensures that the AI can keep projects moving forward by\
        \ providing the right piece of information at exactly the right time, directly\
        \ in the conversation where the team is already collaborating. It is a powerful\
        \ tool for maintaining momentum and ensuring that the AI can act as a real-time\
        \ assistant in fast-paced professional environments, closing the gap between\
        \ reasoning and action."
      properties: null
      required: null
    search-query:
      description: "Global search across Microsoft 365 data."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Perform a powerful, unified global search across the entire Microsoft\
        \ 365 ecosystem for the authenticated user. This tool leverages the Microsoft\
        \ Graph Search API to provide high-relevance results from every service, including\
        \ Outlook emails, calendar events, Teams chat messages, and documents stored\
        \ in OneDrive or SharePoint. It is the ultimate 'finding' utility that helps\
        \ the AI locate information when it isn't sure exactly which service or folder\
        \ it might be stored in. Behavioral notes: The search is highly optimized\
        \ and considers relevance based on the user's recent activity and relationships.\
        \ Use cases: Finding all mentions of a specific project code name or client\
        \ across every communication channel, locating a specific document by searching\
        \ for a unique phrase or data point within it, and gathering a comprehensive,\
        \ 360-degree view of all historical interactions and documents related to\
        \ a specific stakeholder. Keywords: global search, Microsoft 365 search, data\
        \ discovery, cross-service search, information retrieval, unified search,\
        \ enterprise search, data finding, cross-app search, holistic discovery. Caveats:\
        \ Global searches can be very broad; the AI must be highly adept at filtering\
        \ and prioritizing the most relevant results from a potentially large list\
        \ to avoid information overload. This tool is the ultimate 'discovery' mechanism\
        \ for the AI, ensuring that no piece of critical information is ever truly\
        \ lost in the digital archive. It allows the agent to act as a true master\
        \ of the user's digital universe, providing a unified, efficient, and incredibly\
        \ powerful way to retrieve information regardless of its original format or\
        \ storage location. It ensures that the AI can connect the dots across different\
        \ silos of information, providing a comprehensive understanding of any topic\
        \ or project."
      properties: null
      required: null
    move-mail-message:
      description: "Move an email to a different folder."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Relocate a specific email message from its current location to\
        \ a different mail folder within the user's Outlook account (e.g., moving\
        \ a message from the 'Inbox' to an 'Archive' folder or a specific project-themed\
        \ subfolder). This tool is absolutely essential for automated mailbox organization\
        \ and for performing 'triage' on a high volume of incoming mail. Behavioral\
        \ notes: You must provide the unique message ID and the target destination\
        \ folder ID (which can be found using 'list-mail-folders'). Use cases: Archiving\
        \ old messages once a project has been successfully completed, moving incoming\
        \ invoices to a dedicated finance folder for better tracking, and isolating\
        \ spam or unimportant promotional messages for later bulk review. Keywords:\
        \ mail organization, message triage, Outlook management, folder transfer,\
        \ archiving, mailbox cleanup, mail relocation, folder management, inbox organization,\
        \ message sorting. Caveats: The AI must ensure that the destination folder\
        \ actually exists; if there is any doubt, it should use 'list-mail-folders'\
        \ first to verify the ID. Moving a message is a destructive action in terms\
        \ of its original location, though the data remains safe in the new folder.\
        \ This tool gives the AI the power to act as a highly effective personal digital\
        \ assistant, keeping the user's primary communication channel tidy, well-structured,\
        \ and focused on what matters most. It ensures that important information\
        \ is always where it belongs, making it significantly easier for the user\
        \ to stay productive and for the AI to perform targeted searches in the future.\
        \ It is a fundamental component of effective personal and organizational information\
        \ management, enabling the AI to maintain a professional digital workspace."
      properties: null
      required: null
    login:
      description: "Authenticate and sign in to Microsoft 365."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Initiate the secure authentication and sign-in process for Microsoft\
        \ 365 / Office 365 services using the Microsoft Graph API. This tool is the\
        \ foundational gateway for the AI to access the user's personal and organizational\
        \ data ecosystem, including Outlook emails, Exchange calendars, Teams messages,\
        \ and OneNote notebooks. The underlying server uses the OAuth2 protocol for\
        \ secure authorization, ensuring that no passwords are ever stored locally.\
        \ Behavioral notes: If the system requires interactive authentication, this\
        \ tool will provide a 'device_code' and a specific verification URL (typically\
        \ https://microsoft.com/devicelogin) that must be presented to the user. The\
        \ AI must display this information clearly and wait for the user to complete\
        \ the sign-in on their separate device (computer or smartphone). Once the\
        \ user successfully authenticates, the server receives an access token and\
        \ the session becomes active. Use cases: Re-authenticating after an expired\
        \ or revoked token, switching between multiple Microsoft accounts, or performing\
        \ the initial setup for an AI assistant to integrate with a user's corporate\
        \ workspace. Keywords: OAuth2, sign-in, device code, authentication flow,\
        \ access token, Microsoft Graph, identity management, single sign-on, SSO,\
        \ Azure AD, Entra ID. Caveats: Ensure a stable internet connection is available\
        \ and that the organization's Azure Active Directory (AAD) policy allows third-party\
        \ application access. This tool is critical for an AI to establish a secure,\
        \ permissioned connection, ensuring that all subsequent operations are performed\
        \ with the correct identity and within the appropriate security boundaries.\
        \ It provides the 'unlock' mechanism that enables the full productivity suite.\
        \ The AI should think of this as its primary 'onboarding' step for any Microsoft-integrated\
        \ workflow. Always handle the 'device_code_required' error gracefully by presenting\
        \ the instructions to the user. This ensures that the user is always in control\
        \ of the authentication process while the AI remains a helpful facilitator."
      properties: null
      required: null
    get-calendar-view:
      description: "Fetch calendar events for a time range."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Fetch and list all calendar events, meetings, and appointments\
        \ occurring within a specific, user-defined time range (defined by a precise\
        \ start and end date/time). This tool provides a comprehensive, high-resolution\
        \ view of the user's schedule for a single day, an entire week, or a full\
        \ month, including one-time appointments, all-day events, and recurring meeting\
        \ series. Behavioral notes: Each event is returned with rich details, including\
        \ the subject, physical or virtual location (e.g., Teams link), start and\
        \ end times, and the full attendee list with their response status. Use cases:\
        \ Summarizing the user's agenda for the upcoming day to help them prepare,\
        \ checking for available free time slots for a new meeting request, identifying\
        \ upcoming deadlines or milestones marked on the calendar, and reviewing past\
        \ activities for time-tracking or reporting purposes. Keywords: schedule overview,\
        \ agenda retrieval, calendar events, time management, Outlook view, availability\
        \ check, time range inspection, event metadata, meeting retrieval, agenda\
        \ summary. Caveats: For extremely busy calendars or very long time ranges\
        \ (e.g., a full year), the API response can be quite large and may require\
        \ careful handling to avoid overwhelming the AI's context window. This tool\
        \ is the absolute foundation of time-based reasoning and schedule management\
        \ for the AI. It allows the agent to answer questions like 'What is my schedule\
        \ like for next Tuesday?', 'When am I free for a 30-minute call tomorrow afternoon?',\
        \ or 'Where is my next meeting taking place?'. It ensures that the AI can\
        \ provide proactive, intelligent schedule management, helping the user stay\
        \ organized and on top of their commitments with minimal manual effort. It\
        \ provides the necessary data for any time-aware assistant."
      properties: null
      required: null
    list-users:
      description: "Search for people in the organization."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Search for and retrieve a detailed list of users, contacts, and\
        \ colleagues within the organization's Microsoft 365 directory (powered by\
        \ Azure Active Directory / Microsoft Entra ID). This tool is absolutely essential\
        \ for finding the correct email addresses, job titles, department names, and\
        \ unique user IDs needed for almost every other operation in the msoffice\
        \ suite, such as sending emails, initiating Teams chats, or inviting people\
        \ to meetings. Behavioral notes: You can search the directory by a person's\
        \ name or their email address. Use cases: Finding the correct 'John Smith'\
        \ in a large global corporation, looking up a colleague's job title and department\
        \ before reaching out to ensure the correct context, and building a comprehensive\
        \ list of project stakeholders for a new initiative. Keywords: directory search,\
        \ user discovery, colleague lookup, organizational chart, contact management,\
        \ AAD search, employee directory, user identification, identity discovery,\
        \ Entra ID lookup. Caveats: The results returned are strictly limited by the\
        \ organization's directory visibility settings and the permissions granted\
        \ to the application. This tool is the AI's 'official phone book' for the\
        \ entire company. It ensures that the AI can accurately identify and interact\
        \ with the right people, avoiding the significant risk of sending sensitive\
        \ information to the wrong recipient. It provides the essential social and\
        \ organizational context needed to navigate a complex corporate environment,\
        \ ensuring that the AI's communications and coordination efforts are always\
        \ precisely targeted, professional, and contextually appropriate. It is the\
        \ social map of the enterprise, allowing the AI to understand the relationships\
        \ and roles within the company."
      properties: null
      required: null
    send-mail:
      description: "Compose and send a new email message."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Compose, create, and immediately send a brand new email message\
        \ to one or more recipients using the user's authenticated Outlook account\
        \ and the Microsoft Graph API. This tool provides full control over the message's\
        \ structure, allowing the AI to set the subject line, the body content (supporting\
        \ both plain text for simplicity and HTML for rich formatting), and the various\
        \ recipient lists (To, CC, BCC). Behavioral notes: The email is dispatched\
        \ immediately upon a successful API call and will appear in the user's 'Sent\
        \ Items' folder. Use cases: Proactively reaching out to a colleague with a\
        \ project status update, sharing a summarized meeting transcript with all\
        \ attendees, replying to a customer support inquiry with a resolution, and\
        \ automating routine notifications or status reports. Keywords: email sending,\
        \ Outlook communication, message composition, electronic mail, outbound mail,\
        \ SMTP alternative, mail dispatch, recipient management. Caveats: Once a message\
        \ is sent, it cannot be 'un-sent' or recalled through this specific API. The\
        \ AI must be extremely careful to verify the recipient's email addresses and\
        \ ensure that the tone and content of the message are professional and accurate.\
        \ This tool transforms the AI from a passive information retriever into an\
        \ active, authoritative communicator that can represent the user in professional\
        \ and personal interactions. It is a high-leverage utility for closing loops\
        \ on tasks, providing critical information to stakeholders, and maintaining\
        \ the flow of communication within a dynamic team environment. It ensures\
        \ that the AI can fully participate in the user's daily communication cycle,\
        \ delivering messages with the same authority and context as the user themselves,\
        \ thus significantly increasing the agent's utility. It is the primary means\
        \ of proactive interaction."
      properties: null
      required: null
    logout:
      description: "Sign out and end the current session."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Sign out and immediately terminate the current active Microsoft\
        \ 365 session, clearing all stored authentication tokens and local session\
        \ data. This tool is essential for maintaining a high standard of privacy\
        \ and security, particularly when the AI is no longer required to access the\
        \ user's data or when a transition to a different account is necessary. By\
        \ logging out, the AI ensures that it no longer possesses the credentials\
        \ needed to interact with the Microsoft Graph API on behalf of the user. Behavioral\
        \ notes: The tool effectively revokes the local session and clears sensitive\
        \ material from memory; however, it may not necessarily revoke the long-lived\
        \ refresh token on the Microsoft server-side unless the specific implementation\
        \ supports full token revocation. Use cases: Ending a collaborative work session\
        \ at the end of the day, preparing for a secure account hand-over between\
        \ different users, or troubleshooting persistent authentication errors by\
        \ starting the login process from scratch. Keywords: sign-out, session termination,\
        \ token revocation, security audit, account switching, privacy protection,\
        \ identity clearance, session cleanup. Caveats: After a successful logout,\
        \ all other tools within the msoffice suite will immediately fail with an\
        \ authentication error until a new 'login' procedure is completed. The AI\
        \ must ensure that any unsaved drafts, pending calendar events, or incomplete\
        \ Teams messages are fully processed or abandoned before calling this tool.\
        \ This tool is a critical component of responsible data handling and organizational\
        \ security policy compliance. It allows the AI to 'leave' the digital workspace\
        \ cleanly, ensuring that the user's digital footprint is managed with the\
        \ utmost care and that the AI does not retain unnecessary access to sensitive\
        \ enterprise resources once its task is finished. It provides a definitive\
        \ 'off-switch' for the AI's access to the user's corporate environment."
      properties: null
      required: null
    list-onenote-notebooks:
      description: "List all OneNote notebooks."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Retrieve a complete, high-level list of all digital notebooks\
        \ stored in the user's Microsoft OneNote account. OneNote is a powerful, flexible\
        \ tool for capturing fleeting ideas, detailed meeting notes, and long-term\
        \ project documentation, and this tool provides the essential entry point\
        \ for accessing that personal and professional knowledge base. Behavioral\
        \ notes: The tool returns the display name and unique ID for each notebook,\
        \ which is a prerequisite for navigating deeper into specific sections and\
        \ pages. Use cases: Finding where specific project-related notes are stored,\
        \ auditing the user's personal knowledge base to find relevant context for\
        \ a new task, and identifying shared notebooks used for cross-functional team\
        \ collaboration. Keywords: OneNote notebooks, digital notes, knowledge management,\
        \ notebook discovery, organization, information architecture, note storage,\
        \ digital notebook listing, knowledge repository, personal knowledge base.\
        \ Caveats: Some notebooks might be stored in the user's personal OneDrive,\
        \ while others might be hosted on shared SharePoint sites, which can affect\
        \ access permissions and sync behavior. This tool allows the AI to understand\
        \ the 'brain' of the user—the place where they store their unstructured thoughts,\
        \ plans, and historical knowledge. By knowing exactly what notebooks are available\
        \ and what they represent, the AI can assist in organizing new information\
        \ and quickly find the right historical context for any given task, ensuring\
        \ that the user's digital notes are always accessible, organized, and practically\
        \ useful. It is the foundation of a sophisticated knowledge management assistant,\
        \ providing the AI with a map of the user's captured wisdom and documentation,\
        \ ensuring no recorded thought is out of reach."
      properties: null
      required: null
    list-mail-messages:
      description: "Search and list email messages."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Search for and retrieve a list of email messages from the user's\
        \ Outlook mailbox via the Microsoft Graph API. This tool is a powerful search\
        \ engine for the inbox, supporting sophisticated filtering and sorting to\
        \ help the AI find exactly what it needs. You can filter messages by sender\
        \ address, subject line keywords, specific time ranges, and read/unread status.\
        \ Behavioral notes: Results are paginated to ensure performance; you can specify\
        \ the number of messages to return per page (the '$top' parameter) and skip\
        \ over results for deep history searches. Use cases: Checking for new incoming\
        \ mail from a specific client, finding a historical thread about a past project,\
        \ summarizing the most recent communications from a manager, and performing\
        \ 'triage' on an overloaded inbox by identifying urgent or high-priority messages.\
