    get-mail-message:
      description: "Read the full content of an email."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Read and extract the full content, detailed metadata, and technical\
        \ header information for a specific, individual email message in Outlook.\
        \ This tool provides the entire body of the email in multiple formats (typically\
        \ HTML and plain text), allowing the AI to perceive the message exactly as\
        \ the user would. It also includes the full list of recipients (To, CC, BCC),\
        \ precise timestamps, priority levels (Importance), and a flag indicating\
        \ the presence of attachments. Behavioral notes: A valid, unique message ID\
        \ (obtained from 'list-mail-messages') is required as input. Use cases: Analyzing\
        \ the fine details of a project briefing or a legal contract, summarizing\
        \ a long and complex email thread for a quick overview, extracting meeting\
        \ details (time, location, agenda) from an invitation, and identifying the\
        \ exact list of recipients for an old communication to ensure follow-ups are\
        \ correctly addressed. Keywords: email reading, message body, full content\
        \ extraction, mail analysis, Outlook details, message metadata, header inspection,\
        \ recipient analysis. Caveats: Large emails with extensive HTML formatting,\
        \ inline images, or large tables can result in a significant amount of text\
        \ that may consume a large portion of the AI's context window; summarization\
        \ strategies should be employed for very long messages. Note that this tool\
        \ does not return the actual binary content of attachments; it only provides\
        \ the metadata and IDs needed to fetch them with 'list-mail-attachments'.\
        \ This tool is critical for a deep, granular understanding of the user's communications,\
        \ ensuring the AI has all the facts and nuances before responding or taking\
        \ action. It is the cornerstone of informed email assistance, providing the\
        \ raw data needed for complex reasoning, accurate summarization, and high-quality\
        \ drafting. It ensures no detail is missed during analysis."
