    list-chats:
      description: "List active Teams chats."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Retrieve a comprehensive list of all active 1-on-1 and group\
        \ chats in Microsoft Teams for the currently authenticated user. This tool\
        \ provides a high-level, real-time view of the user's instant messaging landscape,\
        \ including the display name of each chat, the list of participating members,\
        \ and the precise timestamp of the very last message sent or received in that\
        \ thread. Behavioral notes: Chats are typically returned sorted by recency,\
        \ allowing the AI to focus on the most active and relevant conversations.\
        \ Use cases: Finding a recent conversation with a specific colleague whose\
        \ name the user might have forgotten, checking for new unread messages in\
        \ a busy group project chat, and mapping out the user's most frequent collaborators\
        \ for organizational insights. Keywords: Teams chats, conversation listing,\
        \ instant messaging, communication history, collaboration, real-time presence,\
        \ chat ID, thread discovery, conversation overview, IM history. Caveats: This\
        \ tool is for discovery only; it returns the metadata and identifiers for\
        \ the chats but does not return the actual message content. The AI must use\
        \ 'list-chat-messages' with a specific chat ID to read the actual discussion\
        \ history. This tool is the essential starting point for any task involving\
        \ the user's Teams-based communications. It allows the AI to navigate the\
        \ fast-paced, often fragmented world of enterprise instant messaging, providing\
        \ a structured way to quickly find and summarize discussions that might otherwise\
        \ be buried under a mountain of notifications. It ensures the AI is aware\
        \ of the 'real-time' heartbeat of the user's professional network, enabling\
