    list-mail-attachments:
      description: "List attachments for a specific email."
      usageIntent: null
      instructions: "Search for and retrieve a detailed, structured list of all files,\
        \ documents, images, and other assets attached to a specific email message\
        \ in Outlook. This tool provides essential metadata for each attachment, including\
        \ the original filename, the file size in bytes, the MIME type (e.g., 'application/pdf',\
        \ 'image/png', 'text/csv'), and a unique attachment ID that can be used for\
        \ further processing or targeted download. Behavioral notes: Crucially, this\
        \ tool does not download the binary content of the file itself; it only provides\
        \ the identifiers and descriptions needed to understand what assets are available\
        \ for analysis. Use cases: Identifying what specific documents were sent along\
        \ with a project proposal, verifying if a received email contains a required\
        \ invoice or receipt, and auditing a long email thread for all shared assets\
        \ to ensure everything has been accounted for. Keywords: email attachments,\
        \ file listing, Outlook assets, document discovery, mail metadata, attachment\
        \ ID, asset inventory, file properties, MIME analysis, attachment search.\
        \ Caveats: You must have the specific message ID from a previous 'list-mail-messages'\
        \ or 'get-mail-message' call to target the correct email. This tool is an\
        \ essential intermediate step for any workflow that involves processing files\
        \ received via email. It allows the AI to 'see' and 'identify' what files\
        \ are available before making a decision on which ones are relevant enough\
        \ to download or analyze further. It ensures that the AI can intelligently\
        \ handle the rich, multi-media nature of modern professional communication,\
        \ bridging the gap between simple text-based messages and complex, document-driven\
        \ business processes. It is a vital tool for any agent performing data extraction\
